'A gaunt-man, you say? It is well that Gúrdring was defeated, and the wights he commanded pushed back. Just such an evil as that might have posed a true threat to Rivendell.\n\n'You have my thanks, [placeholder].'

Defeated wights in Nan Tornaeth ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Calenthon is within Nan Tornaeth, far to the west of Ost Brandras.\n\nCalenthon will be pleased to know that you have slain the gaunt-man Gúrdring.

'The gaunt-man Gúrdring commands the wights of Nan Tornaeth from somewhere deep within the ruins to the north-east, [placeholder]. Search beyond the bridge of Thoniant, and you will surely find his evil.\n\n'Put an end to it, my friend, and we will keep old Rhudaur from rising again.'
'The descendents of Rhudaur will walk Nan Tornaeth forever in payment for their old betrayals.'
